description: This file defines function prototypes for the BreeCpo object related to the BSP Run-time Execution Engine (BREE). It contains declarations for creating, removing, enrolling objects, and initializing the BREE component.

methods.name: BreeCpoCreate
methods.description: Creates an instance of the BREE object, initializing it with container, owner, and reserved contexts.

methods.name: BreeCpoRemove
methods.description: Removes the BREE object instance, freeing resources.

methods.name: BreeCpoEnrollObjects
methods.description: Enrolls or registers necessary objects within the BREE instance.

methods.name: BreeCpoInitialize
methods.description: Initializes the BREE object, setting up internal state and configurations.
